baryon acoustic oscillation distance measurements gives similar constraints: w =-1.027 ± 0.055. Our supernova measurements provide the most stringent constraints to date on the nature of dark energy. Appendices are available in electronic form at {\textless}A href="http://www.aanda.org/10.1051/0004-6361/201423413/olm"{\textgreater}http://www.aanda.org{\textless}/A{\textgreater}Full Table F.3 and covariance matrix are only available at the CDS via anonymous ftp to {\textless}A href="http://cdsarc.u-strasbg.fr"{\textgreater}http://cdsarc.u-strasbg.fr{\textless}/A{\textgreater} (ftp://130.79.128.5) or via {\textless}A href="http://cdsarc.u-strasbg.fr/viz-bin/qcat?J/A+A/568/A22"{\textgreater}http://cdsarc.u-strasbg.fr/viz-bin/qcat?J/A+A/568/A22{\textless}/A{\textgreater}},
